At Egypt 2019 AFCON, many football-loving Nigerians put the blame for Super Eagles defeat to Algeria in the semifinals on the shoulders of goalkeeper Daniel Akpeyi. The situation repeated itself on Sunday at the Stade Rounde Adjio in Garoau, Cameroon.  To some Nigerians, it was a painful exit, especially, after the team had raised the hopes of fans back home. Maduka Okoye (middle) was in goal for Nigeria in the round of 16 clash against Tunisia…on Sunday 